; Golden reference for scripts/eval/statement.txt
; (Axis Magnus Burgundy, card ending 3467, period 20/04–18/05 2026).
; Hand-built by going through all 42 statement rows.
;
; Forex rows: each merchant charge in foreign currency is folded into ONE
; transaction with its markup + GST legs. Pairing was confirmed by the math —
; markup = 2% of the INR billed amount, GST = 18% of the markup — so the
; "FOREIGN CURRENCY TRANSACTION FEE" / "GST" rows (often dated a day later, on
; a different line) map unambiguously back to their merchant.
;
; Skipped as non-user-facing noise: payment summary, balance/limit rows,
; eDGE reward-point balance. No per-txn point accrual is invented — the
; statement only prints a total reward balance, not per-row earn.

